President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Adam J. Szubin as the Under Secretary for Terrorism and Financial Crimes at the Department of the Treasury. Szubin currently serves as the Director of the Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) at the Department of the Treasury. He has also served as the Acting Under Secretary for Terrorism and Financial Crimes at Treasury since February 2015. Szubin has a background in law and has held various positions at the Department of Justice.

President Obama has also announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey J. Hawkins, Jr. as the Ambassador to the Central African Republic. Hawkins is a career member of the Foreign Service and currently serves as the Consul General at the U.S. Consulate in Lagos, Nigeria. He has held various positions within the Department of State, including Director of the Office of South and Central Asian Affairs and Deputy Chief of Mission in Angola.

Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Victoria Esser as the Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of the Treasury. Esser currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Office of Public Affairs at the Treasury Department. She has previous experience in digital strategy and communications, working at the Department of State and various private sector firms.

President Obama expressed his honor and appreciation for these individuals who have chosen to serve the country, highlighting their experience and expertise.